WEBVTT

00:03.985 --> 00:06.750
You know, if I wasn't me,
I would hate me.

00:08.289 --> 00:11.054
Well, I'm not you
and I can see your point.

00:13.061 --> 00:17.829
Oh, man! Who's stinking up
my refrigerator with this octopus?

00:18.833 --> 00:21.393
That's Monique.
She's my date for the hockey game.

00:23.438 --> 00:27.967
Explain to me again why
Red Wing fans throw octopi on the ice.

00:28.376 --> 00:31.141
Because sushi is way
too expensive, honey.

00:32.146 --> 00:34.585
All right, guys, I'll be home by
midnight. What car should I take?

00:34.615 --> 00:37.055
Better take the Nomad. I'm gonna use
the Mustang for the hockey game.

00:37.085 --> 00:39.816
No, you can't take the Nomad.
I'm going to the movies with Patty.

00:39.887 --> 00:41.913
What about the Healey? Is it running?

00:44.192 --> 00:45.930
Guys, what am I supposed to use
for transportation?

00:45.960 --> 00:47.485
Use your bike.

00:49.263 --> 00:50.492
Dad, I'm going on a date.

00:50.565 --> 00:52.470
You ride up to her house,
you ring the bell a couple of times,

00:52.500 --> 00:53.991
chicks dig that stuff.

00:55.336 --> 00:56.360
Guys, this is ridiculous.

00:56.437 --> 00:58.943
I mean, we have three cars
and I still don't have anything to drive.

00:58.973 --> 01:00.545
I mean, when am I going to get
my own car?

01:00.575 --> 01:02.339
We're not gonna just give you
a car, Brad.

01:02.443 --> 01:03.915
Well, Dad, that's why
I've been working so hard.

01:03.945 --> 01:05.470
I mean, I've saved over $2,000.

01:05.546 --> 01:07.606
And on my last report card
I got all A's and B's.

01:07.682 --> 01:09.150
You saved $2,000?

01:09.217 --> 01:11.584
Hold on. You got all A's and B's?

01:13.554 --> 01:15.318
- Yes.
- Really?

01:15.390 --> 01:18.519
I'm proud of you, man.
I'm telling you, that's good work.

01:18.593 --> 01:19.686
But I think this is...

01:19.761 --> 01:22.925
The last thing your mom wants
around here right now is another car.

01:23.030 --> 01:25.590
Actually, I was just thinking that
he's worked very hard

01:25.666 --> 01:27.635
and deserves his own car.

01:28.069 --> 01:29.628
- Really?
- Really?

01:31.005 --> 01:32.443
Well, sure.
I mean, he's saved a lot of money

01:32.473 --> 01:33.778
and we could match that, couldn't we?

01:33.808 --> 01:35.113
- Sure we could match that.
- Yeah!

01:35.143 --> 01:36.681
And on top of that,
I'll spend every waking moment

01:36.711 --> 01:38.441
getting you the best car possible.

01:38.513 --> 01:39.879
- Cool. Thanks.
- Yeah!

01:39.981 --> 01:41.085
- You know what I'm thinking of doing?
- What?

01:41.115 --> 01:43.983
I'll get an old Mercury. I'll chop it.
I'll make a custom out of it.

01:44.051 --> 01:45.781
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!
An old Camaro!

01:45.853 --> 01:47.692
Update it, put a Vette rear end in it.
I got it!

01:47.722 --> 01:48.960
- Dad...
- No. Wait a minute. Stop. Stop.

01:48.990 --> 01:50.027
- I'll go with it...
- Dad.

01:50.057 --> 01:51.396
- Maybe I'll get an off-the-road thing.
- Dad!

01:51.426 --> 01:52.463
- Hold on! Let me...
- Dad!

01:52.493 --> 01:54.359
- What?
- This is my car.

01:54.429 --> 01:55.453
- Yes!
- Yes.

01:55.530 --> 01:56.793
Your car.

01:56.864 --> 01:59.871
Well, I guess I'm gonna call Samantha
and see if she can drive. Thanks, guys.

01:59.901 --> 02:02.373
That's a great idea, matching the funds
for his car. That's wonderful.

02:02.403 --> 02:04.675
Well, I did it 'cause I want him
to have a really cool car,

02:04.705 --> 02:07.265
and money is no object
when it comes to my oldest son

02:07.375 --> 02:10.139
getting a really bitching set of wheels.

02:12.046 --> 02:13.618
The money's coming out
of my car budget, isn't it?

02:13.648 --> 02:14.946
Oh, yeah.

